## 2. Architecture Decisions
_Patterns we follow, things we avoid, key technical choices and their rationale._

<!--
Examples:
- **Pricing rules are versioned and immutable once published** — rollback by activating an older version
- **Redis is cache only; canonical state is always Postgres** — no Redis-first writes
- **All DB migrations require dry-run output before apply** — prevents schema accidents
- **Never use ORM for complex queries** — raw SQL with typed result sets
- **API versioning:** URL-path versioned (/v1/, /v2/) — header versioning rejected (complexity)
-->


